The paper presents a technique for sampling without replacement from randomized programs, including generative neural models that construct outputs sequentially. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions program synthesis and combinatorial optimization, which are topics commonly studied in the programming languages and computation theory (cs.PL) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM) sub-categories. However, since the focus of the paper is on sampling techniques for machine learning models, we consider cs.CL (computational linguistics) and cs.CV (computer vision) to be more likely sub-categories than cs.PL and cs.DM. Finally, the paper's mention of efficiency and scalability suggests that it may also be relevant to the control systems (cs.SY) sub-category.
